Nomad's chronicles - part 3b
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Fascinating as it was, some feared the alien artifact.


The monolith became the subject of heated debates. Two schools of thought emerged from our society.


The first school saw the artifact as a gift, the driver of our progress.


The second school pointed out the dangers of its influence on our minds. The monolith should be destroyed, they said.


Supporters and opponents kept the balance until the first death occurred.